org.bytedeco.javacpp

Class avfilter.AVFilter

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.bytedeco.javacpp.Pointer
      • org.bytedeco.javacpp.avfilter.AVFilter
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    AutoCloseable
    Enclosing class:
    avfilter

    public static class avfilter.AVFilter
extends org.bytedeco.javacpp.Pointer
    Filter definition. This defines the pads a filter contains, and all the callback functions used to interact with the filter.

      • inputs

        @MemberGetter
 @Const
public avfilter.AVFilterPad inputs()
        List of inputs, terminated by a zeroed element. NULL if there are no (static) inputs. Instances of filters with AVFILTER_FLAG_DYNAMIC_INPUTS set may have more inputs than present in this list.

      • outputs

        @MemberGetter
 @Const
public avfilter.AVFilterPad outputs()
        List of outputs, terminated by a zeroed element. NULL if there are no (static) outputs. Instances of filters with AVFILTER_FLAG_DYNAMIC_OUTPUTS set may have more outputs than present in this list.

      • priv_class

        @MemberGetter
 @Const
public avutil.AVClass priv_class()
        A class for the private data, used to declare filter private AVOptions. This field is NULL for filters that do not declare any options. If this field is non-NULL, the first member of the filter private data must be a pointer to AVClass, which will be set by libavfilter generic code to this class.
